==English==
===Etymology===
German ''[[eigen]]'', own + [[function]]

===Noun===
'''eigenfunction''' (''plural'' '''eigenfunctions''')

#{{math}} A [[function]] &phi; such that, for a particular (differential) linear [[operator]] D, D&phi; = &lambda;&phi; where &lambda; is an [[eigenvalue]] of the operator. 
#{{quantum}} An eigenfunctions of the [[Hamiltonian]] operator, representing a [[quantum state]] whose [[energy level]] is given by the corresponding [[eigenvalue]].

====Synonyms====
[[proper function]], [[eigenstate]]

